rrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=14692.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=14692.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top background=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/tableBackground.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/tableBackground.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirkaluvien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Kaluvien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/2/02 9:04:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> Greetings all, for a bit of a challenge and thinking ahead towards the end game, I put all my starting points into wisdom. As a High Elf, I have 120 base wisdom, but my strength is at a lowly 65, stamina and dexterity at only 70, and agility at a decent 85. I'm going in untwinked, so it's not like this can all be fixed by gear straight away. I plan for a tough road, but a well rewarded one towards the upper levels. Please feel free to comment, and let me know if my choice was wise, or not so wise!<br><br>Kaluvien Tallanvor<br>Paladin of Tunare<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1153<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/2/02 11:06:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> It sounds like you understand the situtation.  The points you put into WIS won't help when you start but will help a bunch at L60.  The big reason to increase STR is to carry more especially if you are going to take the intermediate step of Bronze armor(do new Paladins do that anymore?  ayaa...I feel old ^_^). <p><font size="+1">Aeka<br>Level 60 Paladin on Povar<br><font color="#cc00cc">Just don't ask about the purple hair</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utiriantrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirian Trueblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/iconsg.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/2/02 6:28:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirianicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> I played a Paladin to level 28 during the first year of EQ.  Then some friends started playing and no one was a tank, so I deleted my first Paladin and recreated him so I could start with them.  I had put most of my points into STR the first time, but went all 20 into WIS.  I'm only level 55, but I like the extra mana I have, and can't wait until 55 and CC when I think it will make the most difference. <br><br>I restarted with full Ro and Ghoulbane, so I had it easier then you, but if you can manage it, in the long run I think you'll be pleased with the extra 20 WIS.  I know I have been so far. <p><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirsigns.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaauan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aauan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/2/02 10:27:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> i'm 56, and i'd trade my left nut for extra 20 base wis<br><br><br><br><br>---Ariakkas <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52762 </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujcasetn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jcasetn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/3/02 6:22:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> Sounds like a nice plan.  If you can, I'd say twink this guy with a rallic pack, herbalist and archeologist pack.  That way your base str won't be a pain.  My base str is 75 and the constant bank runs and attack penalties from being encumbered were a neverending hassle.  I was sacrificing AC for str items until about level 40 when my gear got me to about 110 and I could replace str rings and such with AC items.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirkaluvien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Kaluvien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/3/02 5:30:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> Sounds like most would agree it was a wise decision. Thanks for the consolation, especially you, Ariakkas! I'm glad that 20 wisdom is worth so much, hehe<br><br>jcasetn, thanks for the advice on equipment... eventually I will be able to afford that kind of gear and it gives me something to look forward to!<br><br>Kaluvien Tallanvor<br>Paladin of Tunare<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uduradam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Duradam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/3/02 6:26:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> Rember, str is usefull for more than just carrying loot.  In grouping with my same group of friends every night, I'm often the only melee, and having a high str raises my atk, lets me deal more damage.  I recently ugreaded from imbued dwarven cultural, to imbued/enchanted, raiseing my str enourmusly. I am well aware that the role of a Paladin is not primarity as a damage dealer, but in our little group it has made a huge diffrence.<br><br>Despite that, I think you did well.  Just rember that +str gear will be as important as weight reduction bags, many times. <p>Duradam Drunkensmythe <BR>Cavalier o' Brell of 52 Virtues<BR>GrandMaster Smithy of 243 Lessons <BR>Arcane And Honor <BR>Druizzl Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1745<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/3/02 8:33:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> The effect of strength on damage is negligible. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6318"><img src="http://www3.sympatico.ca/lchisholm/luth_sig.jpg" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upauloaldeln.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PauloAlDeln</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 4:24:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> Aye, I have a good SK friend who was swearing he would notice a huge difference between 160 STR and 187 STR (getting to 187 STR cost him a good amount of AC too), but when he actually parsed his damage it showed that it was barely making a difference.<br><br>The only time I'd worry about STR is if you're encumbered all the time.<br><br>As for the original question, I think you made the right choice.  I did 10 str, 5 int, 5 wis...I obviously didn't understand EQ stats when I started...I feel the wis loss now, as with my Scaled Knights Helm I'll be questing this week I'll finally be above 100 WIS with my standard AC/HP gear on.<br><br>Paulo <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6350"><IMG SRC="http://home.rochester.rr.com/jeremyfrick/images/paulo_sigfile.jpg" BORDER=0></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaladril1961.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadril1961</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 6:33:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> I like the idea, although I might modify it by putting some of those points into stamina. For me at least it has been much easier to gain plus wisdom items than it has to gain plus stamina items at high level. You'll be missing out on a fair number of hitpoints at high level.  <p><b>Galadril Adamante<BR>Officer, Order of the White Dragon<BR>Knight of Tunare<BR>Bristlebane Server<BR><a href=mailto:sblue@bright.net>sblue@bright.net</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirkaluvien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Kaluvien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 8:55:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> I recently consulted a high level friend who said late game, most Paladin equipment comes loaded with +wisdom and +mana. He informed me that stamina/hp gear is the real killer. Any thoughts?<br><br>Kaluvien Tallanvor<br>Paladin of Tunare<br>Zebuxoruk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 686<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 9:03:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> Yeah as a high elf I've never had any issues with my mana pool. I've always had troubles with encumbrance and my stamina has been pretty poor too. I actually swapped out my valorium greaves for a pair of crusty ones for the 16 sta. So I could get to a whopping 101 sta. heh. <br><br>As a high elf I don't think that putting points into wis is really the best option because that is where we excel at in the first place. Of course you will be a very powerful healer in your later levels. But if you aren't a fast leveller, that could mean a year before you see any benefit from it.<br><br>Personally I think I'd put at least 10 into str as a high elf to get it to 75. I think my base is 77 and even that has caused me lots of heartache over encumbrance. I would say it's better to try to raise all your stats to 75. Everyone knows at 75 you take a huge hit in ac if your agi drops. I would guess that below 75 str you will take a big damage loss, and probably below 75 sta you'll take a big hp drop. If verant is reasonably consistant with their stat system anyway.<br><br>Once you get up in levels, you can focus on different stats relatively easily. Particularly if you are willing to sacrifice a little bit in other areas to do so. So you'll be suffering in your early years from encumbrance and swimming in wis items in your later years and still be encumbered. heh.<br><br><br>Biz.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uphread01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phread01</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.usinternet.com/users/alientro/phread0160.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 9:15:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.usinternet.com/users/alientro/phread0160.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> high elf paladin here.  base str 75 and i will tell you that if you can make it to the higher levels, you have made a good decision (sta still would have been a good idea i think), but have a hard road ahead of you.<br><br>i spent most of my time encumbered, even with all the weight reducing bags i could eventually afford, my armor alone (full bronze at lvl 32 when i became UBER and finally won the roll on a bronze BP in Unrest) encumbered me.  the problem was that this low str kept me from being able to make money as i just couldn't carry as many FS weapons as i should have been able to based on my inventory slots and had to sell more often.  this was costing me hunting time, making me miss more drops, losing more money, and keeping me out of better gear for longer.<br><br>often i had to, at lower levels, pass on equipment upgrades because the better equipment had no str, and i litterally could not afford to give up any str, even for better ac.<br><br>once i hit about lvl 45 or so, i finally had enough money saved up that i could afford to buy some of those decent ac/decent str items that i'd coveted so long and my str problem started to go away.<br><br>now it seems to me that good ac and good str are everywhere, look at barbed ringmail or cc armor...it flows like water and has good ac and good str.  but good ac with good wisdom?  THAT is expensive.<br><br>so anyway, looks like you're going down the path i went down, except you put a lot more into wisdom than i did.  don't give up and dont' get frustrated with your low str.  the way the game is now, you will overcome this much sooner than i did, and your mana pool will be much larger than mine by the time you get into your 50s.<br><br>good luck and best wishes to you. <p><a href="www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=110065">PHREAD</a>, <BR>The Old Man of Torvus Vir<BR>"Life is hard, but it's harder when you're stupid."<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1155<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 9:19:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> It is purely situational.  In exp groups you will need more AC to minimize the downtime and rake more exp.  In raids where you face monsters with wide AE effects you'll want resists and hit points.  In either place you may need to step up and help heal so you will want to have wis/mana gear too. <p><font size="+1">Aeka<br>Level 60 Paladin on Povar<br><font color="#cc00cc">Just don't ask about the purple hair</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uballronholyshield.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ballron Holyshield</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 9:58:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fact or Emotion?</span><hr size=1> There used to be a lot of emotion that said if you had more strength, you were a better melee.  Eventually, parse data was analyzed and the fact was strength had little impact on damage.  So, I ask the same question regarding wisdom.  What do the facts show?  If I had 10 points to wisdom, what tangible benefit do I get?  I believe 10 points of wisdom adds about 100 mana at higher levels.  So whereas I might be oom at 90 wis, I can cast 1 more 100 mana spell at 100 wis.  What spell might that be?  Low mana stun?  Yaulp?  I doubt there is a heal you use that could be fired off with the additional mana gained from extra wisdom.  Yet the extra healing power is the emotion for having higher wisdom.<br><br>My arguement is this, pick the important attributes and ensure you have them covered (i.e. 75 agility to avoid AC decrease, 100 stamina to avoid fatigue impact).  The next most logical place to put your points is stamina as that results in more hit points and is the one stat that has an impact in how &quot;tough&quot; your character is.  Strength and wisdom are emotional stats to bump but I think the facts say otherwise. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1746<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 11:50:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fact or Emotion?</span><hr size=1> Stamina is pretty easy to get if you're on dragon faction.<br>As a high elf, base 75sta 100wis I have:<br><br>137sta +580hp<br>139wis +175mana<br><br>Ballron, wisdom is pretty huge in the end game, particularly on mobs that AE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulargar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Largar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 5:18:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://giant-robot.freeyellow.com/images/giant_robot_head.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fact or Emotion?</span><hr size=1> When I re-rolled my paladin (half elf), I looked at the mana calc on casters realm. At level 60 it shows 900 mana with a 65 wis, and 1200 mana with 90 wis. So I thought hmm, is 300 mana at level 60 worth 25 starting points? <br><br>I guessed it wasnt, and put points into sta and agi, and a few to str. I figured by 60 I'd have an aegis, or a silent watch shield or something better. <br><br>So, now read this post and think hmm, maybe I did bad. Really, am I gonna have troubles when I hit post lvl 50, with a base wis of 65? <p><span style='filter:glow(color=#00FFFF,strength=2);width:100%'>C r u s</span></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utiriantrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirian Trueblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/iconsg.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 5:22:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirianicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fact or Emotion?</span><hr size=1> Not that this fact is a huge factor for putting 20 points into WIS, but the 59th CC spell is less than 300 mana, and I'd wager that one cast will give you many more HP than an extra 20 STA, not to mention those HP can be given to any PC.  <br><br>One other minor advantage of having a higher WIS is reduced fizzle rate.  I know I'm always fizzling, especially when casting my buffs for some reason.  WIS/INT is the stat that helps determine fizzle rate in casters, and I assume it does for hybrids as well.  Can anyone verify this? <p><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirsigns.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalorath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valorath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 7:06:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I would go STA</span><hr size=1> I'm a level 60, well equipped (I think) high elf paladin.  I've got 187 wisdom with my normal set-up, and I put no points into wisdom when I started.  I believe I did all strength.  Maybe stamina but I don't remember, it was almost 3 years ago.  My str is around 170-180ish, and my stamina is 158.  If I could undo the past, I'd take every point I put into strength into stamina, and not think twice about it.  There is so much wisdom gear to be had at the endgame, stamina seems to be my main issue.  Especially having a primal weapon, putting points into strength was a bad idea.  Of course, three years ago I thought I would get more points to put into attributes every time I leveled  *shrug*.<br><br>Here's my equipment, in case you're interested.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://cohort.cc/eqroster/viewchar.php?char=29">cohort.cc/eqroster/viewchar.php?char=29</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>~Val <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 690<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 7:08:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fact or Emotion?</span><hr size=1> Wis will give you technically more hp than sta. but sta will give you a larger hp pool to heal up to anyway. So they are a trade off imo that way.<br><br>Personally I don't think it's a good idea unless you plan to power your character up to 60. If you are going to start off untwinked then it is definitely a better idea to go with a balance of stats to offset your encumbrance at a minimum. <br><br>You'll have a slightly higher mana pool than most, but have been frustrated for half of your game life that you couldn't carry this or that or you were constantly fatigued.<br><br>Once you get to a point where a paladin is really a viable healer you should be able to carry around some extra situational wis gear anyway. <br><br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uekimemsti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ekimemsti</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/4/02 7:18:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.nbnet.nb.ca/hayesm/mini_icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wise, or not so wise?</span><hr size=1> LOL Aauan...what about the right one?<br><br>As for str or wis, I had dumped most of my points<br>into mana as well, and I struggled early in my<br>days with encumberment, but once I could afford<br>a hero bracer and few other str items, I never had<br>a problem. Once I upgraded those items for AC, I <br>simply bought a few weight reduction bags..problem<br>solved as far as encumberment.  Upper levels you<br>will want mana more than str IMHO.  Either way its<br>a game..have fun, and a different choice in some<br>equipment can usually fix some problems with your<br>base stats..<br><br> <p><br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=58933"><img src="http://www3.nbnet.nb.ca/hayesm/sig_final.gif" alt="Click here for my Magelo Profile"></p><i></i></td></tr></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=14692.topic&start=21&stop=25>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=14692.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=14692.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14692.topic&index=20><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/repl